commit_message:
Create ChIP_motif.r

This script is used for illustrating a scatter plot from de novo motif analysis by Homer 

library(dplyr)

Create ChIP_genes.r

This script is for assigning ChIP peaks to nearest genes (within 100kb of TSS of nearest genes)

Create ChIP_bed_filter.r

This script is for filtering ChIPseq peaks for further analysis

Create makeUCSCfiles.slurm

This is a script used for making files in UCSC genome browser. Before running this, you need to perform makeTagDirectory.slrum and findPeak.slurm first.

Create findPeak.slurm

This is Homer finding peaks script. Before running this, makeTagDirectory.slurm used be performed first.

Create makeTagDirectory.slurm

This is a script used for making Tag directory. This process is required if you use Homer as the peak finder. The script first creates a directory for each chromosome. Then this script finds "accepted hits" while annotating which chromosome this hit comes from at the same time. The "accepted hit" means a mapped NGS read. Finally, it allocates each "accepted hits" to the chromosome directory it created before.

Create tophat2.slurm

This is script for mapping NGS data to mouse genome (mm10).

Create cutadapt.slurm

Script for cutting adapters.

Create multiqc.slurm

This is script for integrate QC result.

Create fastqc.slurm

This script is used for checking quality of sequence files.

Create sra_download.slurm

Scripts for download data from GEO database.
